main event: A civilian reported sighting 16 objects flying in formation in Sacramento, California on 31 May 1949. The objects were later concluded to be birds.
interesting points: The observer reported 16 objects flying in formation, which disappeared and reappeared three different times.
The objects were described as having the same color as the clouds and were observed at a height of 25,000 feet.
The observer mistook the flying birds for a 'formation of flying saucers', highlighting the misidentification of the objects.
The observer mentioned the presence of white cranes in the area but noted that they had never seen them fly in formation in 22 years.
There were uncertainties around the identity of the observed objects, leading to the involvement of technical intelligence division for analysis.
